</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,258,966]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,871,895]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[324,431,870,895]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decliva" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[324,431,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">J. decliva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[438,528,871,895]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[438,528,871,895]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has the male pygofer similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Cai &amp; He" authorityName="Cai &amp; He" box="[970,1177,870,895]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longa">
<emphasis box="[970,1060,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">J. longa</emphasis>
Cai &amp; He
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having a greatly reduced dorsal apodeme and preatrium, a subapical ridge on the ventral margin of the aedeagal shaft and median lateral flanges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
